stylometry: Our group project was a cost simulation for Ruby Tuesday.  Mike Kren works as a server so we thought we would use Ruby tuesday since we had accces to information to complete our model.  The problem: to many servers were on at once and each servers utilization was at like 10%.  So we figured we could run this simulation to find a more cost efffective way for Ruby Tuesday to run on tuesdays.  We took the information from 4 tuesdays so one month.  We took the averages of arrival rate of customers and how many tables servers can handle.  we then ran the calculations and showed the answers through 1-8 servers.  We found 3 servers were the best to have on the lunch rush for tuesdays.  the server utilization was around 50% which is perfect.  I learned a real application that I can use in life.  I learned server utilization. We all worked on the project together and did everything together as a group so its hard to say what we actually did.
